OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA wet start to the day across
OL,6,Fwestern parts of Wales. Dry but rather
OL,7,Fcloudy in the east. Rain slowly
OL,8,Fspreading eastwards as the day
OL,9,Fprogresses, with brighter skies
OL,10,Ffollowing into the west for the
OL,11,Fafternoon. Winds easing.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FRain soon moving away this
OL,14,Fevening, with clear spells following.
OL,15,FA few showers are possible overnight,
OL,16,Fthough most staying dry. Turning
OL,17,Fchilly where skies remain clear.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
